race.comment: BOLD ARTIC (2) wound up strongly at the end of 1200m at Rockhampton last time out, beaten just 0.7L. He was good at the Sunshine Coast the one before also in stronger. Fitter again and well placed with the 3kg claim. SPIRIT OF NURAI (11) was second-up and spiked her figures beaten a nose here over 1200m in a CL2. Has a 1.5kg claim in easier and will be further improved. Can make the finish with average luck from the awkward gate. INTRUDER (3) peaks and has a key gear switch. This is a bit tougher but he's going well enough to get into the frame. THE BOSS MAN (5) is a former Victorian who resumed with a tidy Maiden win at Rockhampton. Has more to give and has an inside gate and a handy 2kg claim. The tongue tie is on for the first time and keep him onside.
